yourself, Joseph, you ambitious boy!

70
00:07:01,840 --> 00:07:03,840
- You son of a-
- Joseph!

71
00:07:03,840 --> 00:07:05,840
Jesus and the saints preserve us!

72
00:07:07,960 --> 00:07:09,600
We thought you died, Da.

73
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:12,760
l did, son.
l passed away.

74
00:07:12,760 --> 00:07:15,160
But you're talking to us, Da.

75
00:07:15,160 --> 00:07:17,360
And your eyes-
they're looking about.

76
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:19,760
l was as dead as a stone,
l tell you.

77
00:07:19,760 --> 00:07:22,920
Now shut your mouth
before l die again.

78
00:07:22,920 --> 00:07:25,600
Well, l am-

79
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:29,080
Come here!

80
00:07:29,080 --> 00:07:31,560
l've come back
to tell you something.

81
00:07:37,320 --> 00:07:40,560
You're an especially odd boy.

82
00:07:42,760 --> 00:07:45,920
You came back from the dead
to tell me that l'm odd?

83
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:49,280
You have all kinds of oddities...

84
00:07:49,280 --> 00:07:51,320
clattering around in your brain.

85
00:07:51,320 --> 00:07:54,200
So had l when l was as young as you.

86
00:07:54,200 --> 00:07:58,520
But dreams, my boy,
in this poor corner of the world...

87
00:07:58,520 --> 00:08:00,240
end up in a glass of ale.

88
00:08:01,560 --> 00:08:04,920
No. Not my dreams, Da.

89
00:08:04,920 --> 00:08:06,840
l'll work my own land someday.

90
00:08:06,840 --> 00:08:11,160
Without land, a man is nothing.

91
00:08:11,160 --> 00:08:13,560
That's it. Yeah.

92
00:08:14,720 --> 00:08:19,200
Land is a man's very own soul.

93
00:08:22,760 --> 00:08:25,920
A miracle-
that's what you're looking for.

94
00:08:25,920 --> 00:08:31,120
And by God, if you manage it...

95
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:34,360
your old da will be
smiling down on you...

96
00:08:34,360 --> 00:08:35,800
from heaven above.

97
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:41,080
Her beautiful eyes

98
