Were a terrible

99
00:09:08,880 --> 00:09:12,360
God bless your soul, Joe Donelly...

100
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:14,640
for the second time.

101
00:09:14,640 --> 00:09:16,840
God rest your soul, Da.

102
00:10:10,160 --> 00:10:13,240
Say nothing to them, lads.

103
00:10:13,240 --> 00:10:16,720
This country's ours.
They don't exist.

104
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:24,680
What dead man is this?

105
00:10:34,040 --> 00:10:36,920
You needn't answer,
but hear these words.

106
00:10:36,920 --> 00:10:40,760
l represent Mr. Daniel Christie,
who by right of law...

107
00:10:40,880 --> 00:10:43,640
owns this land
and all improvements upon it.

108
00:10:47,280 --> 00:10:49,480
Rent on this property
has not been paid.

109
00:10:49,480 --> 00:10:52,480
The warning's been given thrice.

110
00:10:57,640 --> 00:11:01,400
Keep walking, lads.
Our father's being buried today.

111
00:11:07,240 --> 00:11:08,760
Bastards are burning our house!

112
00:11:11,760 --> 00:11:13,680
That will do.

113
00:11:18,160 --> 00:11:20,200
Where is this landlord Christie?

114
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:22,400
l want justice for what he's done.

115
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:43,120
There's nothing l like better...

116
00:11:43,120 --> 00:11:46,640
than the glow of murder
in a young fellow's eyes.

117
00:11:46,640 --> 00:11:48,760
lt has a terrible go of rust on it.

118
00:11:51,280 --> 00:11:52,880
l've only killed chickens and pigs
till now.

119
00:11:52,880 --> 00:11:58,360
He's a pig and a chicken in one,
the same Daniel Christie.

120
00:11:58,360 --> 00:12:01,800
Here, now.
Give him a proper taste of death.

121
00:12:03,840 --> 00:12:06,720
Yeah. Landlords.

122
00:12:11,120 --> 00:12:12,840
Captain Moonlight.

123
00:12:17,640 --> 00:12:21,280
Don't pretend you know what Captain
Moonlight means, 'cause you don't.

124
00:12:21,280 --> 00:12:24,560
lt's the code, the rebel code.

125
00:12:24,560 --> 00:12:27,400
Now that you've heard it,
keep it to yourself.

126
00:12:27,400 --> 00:12:30,400
Don't breathe it to a living soul.
Do you understand?

127
00:12:36,040 --> 00:12:37,960
Captain Moonlight, Joseph.

128
00:12:39,040 --> 00:12:41,400
Off to kill your landlord, eh?

129
00:12:43,040 --> 00:12:45,720
Blow the bastard's head off!

130
00:12:45,720 --> 00:12:47,640
Don't be afraid to kill him.

131
00:12:48,800 --> 00:12:51,400
Assassinate the bastard!

132
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:57,520
lt was too good to be kept a secret.

133
00:12:59,440 --> 00:13:01,960
Do you know which end of the gun
to point at the gentleman?

134
00:13:01,960 --> 00:13:04,840
He'll shoot himself in the balls,
l'll wager...

135
00:13:04,840 --> 00:13:06,840
and come hobbling home in tears.

136
00:13:08,160 --> 00:13:10,880
Good-bye, Colm.
Good-bye, Paddy.

137
00:13:10,880 --> 00:13:13,720
Good-bye, Joseph.
We'll see you at your wake.

138
00:15:01,920 --> 00:15:04,120
God bless all in this house.

139
00:15:04,120 --> 00:15:05,640
God bless you, son.

140
00:15:17,560 --> 00:15:19,680
Down from the north, are you?

141
00:15:23,480 --> 00:15:26,280
Or perhaps the east?

142
00:15:28,280 --> 00:15:30,960
West of here, maybe?

143
00:15:30,960 --> 00:15:32,880
South.

144
00:15:32,880 --> 00:15:35,760
l prefer to keep my business
to myself, if you please.

145
00:15:35,760 --> 00:15:37,200
Very wise.

146
00:15:39,880 --> 00:15:41,800
God bless you, everyone.

147
00:15:41,800 --> 00:15:43,720
Ah, bless you, sir.

148
00:15:45,440 --> 00:15:48,440
- Whiskey for everyone!
- Oh, great!

149
00:15:51,320 --> 00:15:53,040
How are you, sir, tonight?

150
00:15:53,040 --> 00:15:54,360
Oppressed.

151
00:15:55,440 --> 00:15:57,440
That's the word for me.

152
00:15:57,440 --> 00:16:00,720
l live in a house
that's stuffy and dull...

153
00:16:00,720 --> 00:16:03,400
and worse, l've a wife
who forbids me to drink.

154
00:16:03,400 --> 00:16:06,280
- God help you.
- l crave adventure, boys.

155
00:16:06,280 --> 00:16:10,120
lf l had wings,
l'd fly to the stars.

156
00:16:10,280 --> 00:16:12,880
Your good health, sir.

157
00:16:12,880 --> 00:16:14,600
Good health, Mr. Christie.

158
00:16:26,880 --> 00:16:28,440
Liven up, lad.

159
00:16:28,440 --> 00:16:31,800
You're too young to be brooding
in your ale.

160
00:16:34,280 --> 00:16:37,920
What places you
in this small chapter of the world?

161
00:16:38,960 --> 00:16:42,600
He's keeping himself to himself,
that one.

162
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:44,840
Oh, then it's one of two things:

163
00:16:44,840 --> 00:16:46,280
enterprise or love.

164
00:16:46,280 --> 00:16:49,520
lt isn't love.
Rest assured of that.

165
00:16:49,520 --> 00:16:51,440
Then you're a man of business...

166
00:16:51,440 --> 00:16:53,280
like myself.

167
00:16:54,240 --> 00:16:56,800
But l warn you...

168
00:16:56,800 --> 00:16:59,600
it's brought me nothing but misery.

169
00:16:59,600 --> 00:17:02,360
l'm lost in a fog
of commerce and compromise.

170
00:17:02,360 --> 00:17:06,880
l'd trade it all away
for 15 minutes of freedom.

171
00:17:10,720 --> 00:17:13,400
Freedom is a rare thing
in these parts.

172
00:17:16,200 --> 00:17:18,280
lt is.

173
00:17:18,280 --> 00:17:21,280
- lt is, indeed.
- Oh, indeed it is.

174
00:17:26,080 --> 00:17:28,160
To a long and happy life...

175
00:17:28,160 --> 00:17:29,800
Mr. Christie.

176
00:17:29,800 --> 00:17:31,720
God bless you, lad.

177
00:17:38,320 --> 00:17:41,320
Why should l expire

178
00:17:41,320 --> 00:17:44,880
For the fire of any eye

179
00:17:45,920 --> 00:17:48,600
Though foolish men you slay

180
00:17:48,600 --> 00:17:50,440
For thee l shall not die

181
00:17:55,880 --> 00:17:59,360
Your beauty and your name

182
00:17:59,360 --> 00:18:02,520
Will never conquer me

183
00:18:02,520 --> 00:18:04,440
What have l done

184
00:18:10,760 --> 00:18:12,000
Hello...

185
00:18:12,880 --> 00:18:16,400
souls of the departed...

186
00:18:16,400 --> 00:18:20,240
what a disappointment
l must seem to you all.

187
00:18:30,320 --> 00:18:33,760
Oh, no. Here we are- home.

188
00:18:33,760 --> 00:18:37,240
l recognize these hedges
by their dullness.

189
00:18:39,040 --> 00:18:41,640
O woman, high of fame

190
00:18:41,640 --> 00:18:45,280
Though men have died for thee

191
00:19:07,520 --> 00:19:09,920
This is a difficult murder.

192
00:19:15,880 --> 00:19:18,160
Good evening, Mr. Christie.

193
00:19:18,160 --> 00:19:19,920
Take the horse.

194
00:19:54,320 --> 00:19:57,320
Shannon, l saw you galloping
in the fields.

195
00:19:58,280 --> 00:20:00,840
Dignity, Shannon, Dignity.

196
00:20:00,840 --> 00:20:04,960
A lady must always be civilized,
even when she rides.

197
00:20:04,960 --> 00:20:06,320
No one saw me riding, Mother.

198
00:20:06,320 --> 00:20:09,280
- l saw you!
- Yes, Mother.

199
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:24,080
''A lady must always be civilized.''

200
00:20:24,080 --> 00:20:26,760
She never leaves us alone,
does she?

201
00:20:26,760 --> 00:20:29,240
No, she doesn't.

202
00:20:29,240 --> 00:20:31,840
There. Go on. Good girl.

203
00:21:09,120 --> 00:21:10,880
ls somebody there?

204
00:21:48,080 --> 00:21:49,880
Stay right where you are.

205
00:21:49,880 --> 00:21:52,480
Don't flutter an eyelid
or l'll stab you.

206
00:21:52,480 --> 00:21:53,720
l'll stab you through.

207
00:22:12,720 --> 00:22:13,960
Father!

208
00:22:17,240 --> 00:22:18,360
Jesus!

209
00:22:34,000 --> 00:22:36,040
Father, help!

210
00:22:37,360 --> 00:22:40,040
l've been all but raped
and slaughtered!

211
00:22:40,040 --> 00:22:42,160
- What is it?
- ln the stables!

212
00:22:42,160 --> 00:22:44,000
- What's the fuss about?
- lt's the devil himself!

213
00:22:45,800 --> 00:22:48,200
- Mr. Daniel Christie!
- Oh, my God!

214
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:50,400
Look!

215
00:22:50,400 --> 00:22:51,640
Yes?

216
00:22:51,640 --> 00:22:54,360
l'm Joseph Donelly...

217
00:22:54,360 --> 00:22:57,800
of the family Donelly
that you pushed off our land.

218
00:22:57,800 --> 00:23:00,080
What in the name of God
are you talking about?

219
00:23:00,080 --> 00:23:03,360
Prepare to pay for your crimes.

220
00:23:06,120 --> 00:23:08,440
Good Lord Jesus!

221
00:23:16,880 --> 00:23:19,480
Captain Moonlight.

222
00:23:20,720 --> 00:23:23,000
Shannon, come back!

223
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:25,600
Quickly, find Mr. Chase
and bring him here. Go!

224
00:23:28,280 --> 00:23:30,200
Shannon, come inside.

225
00:23:31,280 --> 00:23:33,200
Shannon, turn around.

226
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:42,760
Look how black his fingers are,
Mother.

227
00:23:42,760 --> 00:23:46,880
Never mind his fingers.
He's a lowborn blatherskite of filth.

228
00:23:48,240 --> 00:23:50,920
lf he's so worthless, then why are you
bothering to dress his wounds?

229
00:23:50,920 --> 00:23:53,600
Our duty is to restore him
to full health...

230
00:23:53,600 --> 00:23:57,240
so he can hear his own neck crack when
he dangles from the hangman's noose.

231
00:23:59,000 --> 00:24:02,320
Turn away, Shannon,
and protect the innocence of your eyes.

232
00:24:04,080 --> 00:24:07,920
Of all the days
to intrude upon our peaceful life.

233
00:24:07,920 --> 00:24:11,160
The ladies are coming by
this afternoon for tea.

234
00:24:11,160 --> 00:24:13,840
l'm feeling very sick
all of a sudden.

235
00:24:13,840 --> 00:24:18,360
Mind yourself, Shannon. Those ladies are
models of manners and behavior.

236
00:24:18,360 --> 00:24:19,400
There.

237
00:24:23,920 --> 00:24:27,760
- Nothing happened!
- Nothing happened, indeed.

238
00:24:31,320 --> 00:24:34,840
A poor, misguided robin has
broken a windowpane.

239
00:24:34,840 --> 00:24:36,880
What a manufactured lie.

240
00:24:36,880 --> 00:24:39,280
l was merely dusting
the liquor cabinet.

241
00:24:39,280 --> 00:24:42,720
As if a bottle in your vicinity
stood long enough to gather dust.

242
00:24:42,720 --> 00:24:44,920
Now, go upstairs.
l can manage in here.

243
00:24:44,920 --> 00:24:46,920
Oh, look at what you've done.

244
00:24:48,760 --> 00:24:52,600
Mary, Mary, Mary Nell

245
00:24:52,600 --> 00:24:57,080
Do you hear your wedding bell

246
00:24:57,080 --> 00:25:01,600
Will he love you, Mary Nell

247
00:25:01,600 --> 00:25:04,760
Time and time alone will tell

248
00:25:47,720 --> 00:25:50,520
You're having a dream.
This isn't really happening.

249
00:25:51,200 --> 00:25:55,320
l want my land!

250
00:26:09,680 --> 00:26:13,240
What became of the man l married?

251
00:26:13,240 --> 00:26:16,120
Some other man's replaced him
and goes about with his name.

252
00:26:19,560 --> 00:26:23,320
A murderous insurgent
under your own roof!

253
00:26:23,320 --> 00:26:24,960
How horrible!

254
00:26:24,960 --> 00:26:27,040
He's as ugly as sin...

255
00:26:27,040 --> 00:26:29,920
and the most vicious creature
l've ever set eyes upon.

256
00:26:32,440 --> 00:26:34,520
Did you get a look at him, Shannon?

257
00:26:38,560 --> 00:26:40,400
A peek.

258
00:26:40,400 --> 00:26:42,680
Shannon, what is your collar doing?

259
00:26:42,680 --> 00:26:45,360
- lt's choking me.
- Well, do it up.

260
00:26:45,360 --> 00:26:47,760
Better to choke
than to be vulgar.

261
00:26:49,680 --> 00:26:51,720
l hear a noise.

262
00:26:51,720 --> 00:26:53,240
Let us hope it's Stephen Chase.

263
00:26:53,240 --> 00:26:55,560
We've come for your prisoner,
Mr. Christie.

264
00:26:56,960 --> 00:26:58,880
Good afternoon, Mrs. Christie.

265
00:26:58,880 --> 00:27:00,800
Good afternoon, ladies.

266
00:27:03,800 --> 00:27:06,200
Speak of the sun
and we see its rays.

267
00:27:06,200 --> 00:27:08,880
Oh, my goodness,
we were so frightened.

268
00:27:08,880 --> 00:27:11,360
Keep calm.
You're safe and protected.

269
00:27:11,360 --> 00:27:13,680
Go back to your sinful card playing.

270
00:27:17,520 --> 00:27:18,760
Hello, Shannon.

271
00:27:21,920 --> 00:27:23,240
Hello, Stephen.

272
00:27:26,520 --> 00:27:28,720
My, how handsome he is.

273
00:27:28,720 --> 00:27:31,320
He's a brilliant young man.
He was educated at Trinity.

274
00:27:31,320 --> 00:27:32,840
Of course.

275
00:27:32,840 --> 00:27:35,840
He manages all my husband's
business affairs.

276
00:27:35,840 --> 00:27:38,040
Your daughter is certainly
a very lucky girl.

277
00:27:38,040 --> 00:27:40,040
Yes, indeed.

278
00:28:01,720 --> 00:28:06,400
Shannon, the ladies and l
would like you to play the piano.

279
00:28:12,640 --> 00:28:14,000
l beg your pardon?

280
00:28:15,520 --> 00:28:18,680
Come play something, Shannon.
Something fanciful and nice.

281
00:28:51,680 --> 00:28:53,600
She plays beautifully.

282
00:29:13,560 --> 00:29:15,360
Good gracious, child.

283
00:29:15,360 --> 00:29:18,520
- lt's band music, Mother.
- ''Band music''?

284
00:29:18,520 --> 00:29:21,880
lt's very modern.
lt's from America.

285
00:29:51,920 --> 00:29:53,520
Shannon, stay back.

286
00:29:57,200 --> 00:29:59,480
Careful, boy.
Your life's worth little as it is.

287
00:30:02,160 --> 00:30:06,280
You're the bastard
that burned my father's house.

288
00:30:08,120 --> 00:30:11,680
l've burned many houses in the line
of duty. Am l meant to remember yours?

289
00:30:18,200 --> 00:30:20,480
Maybe you'll remember this.

290
00:30:29,680 --> 00:30:32,080
Pistols, tomorrow at dawn.

291
00:30:34,200 --> 00:30:36,040
Get him upstairs!

292
00:30:40,440 --> 00:30:41,600
Go on.

293
00:30:51,080 --> 00:30:55,200
Come, ladies. Let us resume
our pleasantries in the parlor.

294
00:30:55,200 --> 00:30:57,680
Come, dear.
You, too, Shannon.

295
00:31:05,080 --> 00:31:07,960
What's buzzing around inside
that head of yours, my little monkey?

296
00:31:10,160 --> 00:31:12,360
The day's been disrupted, Father.

297
00:31:14,400 --> 00:31:15,840
Heaven forbid.

298
00:31:53,600 --> 00:31:55,640
l'm running away.

299
00:32:03,880 --> 00:32:05,120
Excuse me.

300
00:32:07,600 --> 00:32:09,920
There's something in here l need.

301
00:32:15,200 --> 00:32:19,040
Perhaps you're wondering
why l'm running away.

302
00:32:20,960 --> 00:32:22,560
Well, l'll tell you.

303
00:32:22,560 --> 00:32:26,040
l'm running away
because l'm modern.

304
00:32:26,040 --> 00:32:29,880
l'm modern,
and l'm going to a modern place.

305
00:32:29,960 --> 00:32:32,160
You're not the only one
who's trapped.

306
00:32:33,200 --> 00:32:37,520
lf l stay here, my mother will turn me
into one of her stuffy old friends.

307
00:32:38,880 --> 00:32:42,320
No, thank you.
l'm a little more interesting than that.

308
00:32:44,920 --> 00:32:48,760
l'm very smart, and l'm very modern.
That's all you need to know about me.

309
00:32:50,760 --> 00:32:52,000
Boy, here!

310
00:32:52,000 --> 00:32:53,920
Have a look at this.

311
00:32:55,000 --> 00:32:56,040
Look.

312
00:33:01,520 --> 00:33:04,280
You can't read, can you?
How pathetic.

313
00:33:06,480 --> 00:33:08,800
''Land,'' it says.

314
00:33:10,240 --> 00:33:11,280
''Land''?

315
00:33:13,120 --> 00:33:15,800
''Wanted:
strong, healthy men and women.

316
00:33:15,800 --> 00:33:21,160
Every resident of the United States
is entitled to 160 acres of land.''

317
00:33:21,160 --> 00:33:23,480
They've got so much of it
they give it away for free.

318
00:33:27,520 --> 00:33:29,880
No land is given away...

319
00:33:29,880 --> 00:33:31,920
in any part of the world.

320
00:33:32,960 --> 00:33:34,520
ln America it is...

321
00:33:34,520 --> 00:33:36,800
and l'm going there.

322
00:33:36,800 --> 00:33:38,800
l'm going to have
a place of my own.

323
00:33:38,800 --> 00:33:41,120
And l will have horses on it,
and l will raise them...

324
00:33:41,120 --> 00:33:43,920
and l will ride them
any way l please.

325
00:33:43,920 --> 00:33:47,640
What do you need more land for?
You own half of lreland as it is!

326
00:33:47,640 --> 00:33:49,640
You took it, your people did!

327
00:33:51,280 --> 00:33:53,200
l didn't take it.

328
00:33:53,200 --> 00:33:57,040
You just live here
all fancied up on rent...

329
00:33:57,040 --> 00:33:59,240
and broken backs.

330
00:33:59,240 --> 00:34:02,040
Boy, you said you wanted land.

331
00:34:02,040 --> 00:34:05,400
lf that's what you want,
then come with me.

332
00:34:06,640 --> 00:34:09,680
Great ships sail
out of Dublin and Liverpool.

333
00:34:09,680 --> 00:34:11,440
But a woman dare not travel alone.

334
00:34:11,440 --> 00:34:15,280
You're brave. You shoot men,
you step on their necks.

335
00:34:15,440 --> 00:34:19,760
When l saw that, l realized
you could be very useful to me.

336
00:34:19,760 --> 00:34:22,920
- Useful, could l?
- Yes! You could be my serving boy.

337
00:34:24,280 --> 00:34:26,280
Oh, l see.

338
00:34:28,400 --> 00:34:30,320
l could polish your boots for you.

339
00:34:30,320 --> 00:34:32,720
They will need a polish
now and then.

340
00:34:33,760 --> 00:34:37,240
Aye, they would.
And l could make you a cup of tea.

341
00:34:38,280 --> 00:34:40,000
When teatime calls for it, yes.

342
00:34:40,000 --> 00:34:43,840
l'll throw the tea in your face and l'll
piss on your boots before l serve you!

343
00:34:43,920 --> 00:34:45,080
Get out!

344
00:34:46,040 --> 00:34:48,240
- l'll pay you threepence a day.
- Get out!

345
00:34:48,240 --> 00:34:51,120
l've got an appointment in the morning,
and l'm going to honor it.

346
00:34:51,120 --> 00:34:53,720
Ha! You'll never win this duel
with Stephen.

347
00:34:53,720 --> 00:34:57,280
We've all seen you handle a gun.
Boy, l am giving you your freedom!

348
00:34:57,280 --> 00:34:59,280
l'm not going to a distant world.

349
00:34:59,280 --> 00:35:02,240
l'm of lreland,
and l'll stay in lreland till l die.

350
00:35:02,240 --> 00:35:04,160
That's in about five hours.

351
00:35:21,040 --> 00:35:23,160
These weapons belonged
to my father's father.

352
00:35:28,160 --> 00:35:30,440
His father's father was an ass.

353
00:35:34,280 --> 00:35:38,040
l've asked to serve as your second
in this barbarism.

354
00:35:39,640 --> 00:35:41,680
l appreciate that, sir.

355
00:35:41,680 --> 00:35:43,480
Choose one of those things.

356
00:35:51,920 --> 00:35:54,040
You had a good breakfast this morning,
did you?

357
00:35:57,120 --> 00:36:00,000
- lt was grand, sir. Thank you.
- Good.

358
00:36:00,000 --> 00:36:02,960
Count away 15 paces.

359
00:36:04,480 --> 00:36:08,920
- One, two.
- This way, son.

360
00:36:08,920 --> 00:36:11,800
- Three, four-
- Ah, fog.

361
00:36:11,800 --> 00:36:14,840
My life is one long mollifying fog.

362
00:36:14,840 --> 00:36:17,440
The land l hold, l inherited.

363
00:36:17,440 --> 00:36:20,720
lt manages itself
with a foggy logic of its own.

364
00:36:20,720 --> 00:36:25,120
Son, l was up thinking about you
all night long.

365
00:36:25,120 --> 00:36:29,440
l knew nothing of your family or their
eviction. l'm sorry for their pain.

366
00:36:29,440 --> 00:36:34,520
l understand why you came to murder me,
and l don't blame you for it at all.

367
00:36:34,520 --> 00:36:36,320
Fifteen!

368
00:36:36,320 --> 00:36:38,080
Turn, each man, and fire!

369
00:36:45,440 --> 00:36:46,880
l can't see anything!

370
00:36:46,880 --> 00:36:48,600
l can.

371
00:36:52,160 --> 00:36:54,480
Boy! Come away from there!

372
00:36:54,480 --> 00:36:56,480
Shannon, get out of the way!

373
00:36:56,480 --> 00:36:59,720
- Assess your stupidity, lad.
- Get away from me, woman!

374
00:36:59,720 --> 00:37:01,160
As you wish.

375
00:37:08,000 --> 00:37:09,520
- Wait!
- Shannon!

376
00:37:15,640 --> 00:37:17,000
Shannon, don't!

377
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:18,360
Good-bye, Stephen.

378
00:37:18,360 --> 00:37:21,320
''Good-bye''? Don't shoot!

379
00:37:29,960 --> 00:37:32,360
l saved your neck.
You remember that.

380
00:37:56,400 --> 00:37:57,360
Afternoon.

381
00:37:58,520 --> 00:38:01,880
- Thank you, boy.
- Don't call me ''boy.''

382
00:38:01,880 --> 00:38:02,920
Sugar.

383
00:38:12,240 --> 00:38:13,280
Two.

384
00:38:20,960 --> 00:38:24,800
You might display some gratitude
considering l paid for your passage.

385
00:38:24,880 --> 00:38:27,480
l paid, let me remind you.

386
00:38:31,040 --> 00:38:33,440
Oh, good afternoon.

387
00:38:33,440 --> 00:38:35,560
Forgive me if l'm intruding,
but l wonder...

388
00:38:35,560 --> 00:38:37,960
if you'd enjoy a gentle stroll
around the deck.

389
00:38:37,960 --> 00:38:39,560
She's drinking her tea now.

390
00:38:39,560 --> 00:38:41,600
There's no need
to state the obvious, boy.

391
00:38:42,640 --> 00:38:45,520
My name's McGuire,
from Boston, Massachusetts.

392
00:38:47,240 --> 00:38:49,360
Oh, you're American.

393
00:38:49,360 --> 00:38:53,080
lrish born.
l went back for personal reasons.

394
00:38:53,080 --> 00:38:55,480
A stroll would be delightful,
Mr. McGuire.

395
00:38:59,040 --> 00:39:00,080
Parasol.

396
00:39:02,480 --> 00:39:07,080
ln my imagination,
America is a wonderfully modern place.

397
00:39:07,080 --> 00:39:09,480
- Am l right?
- Modern as modern can be.

398
00:39:09,480 --> 00:39:11,880
The people, the culture,
the industry.

399
00:39:11,880 --> 00:39:15,160
- What about the land?
- l beg your pardon?

400
00:39:15,160 --> 00:39:18,240
This girl's got it in her head
that they're giving land away for free.

401
00:39:18,240 --> 00:39:21,760
That's true. Oklahoma territory.
The west's opening up.

402
00:39:21,760 --> 00:39:24,560
- l told you, boy.
- Can't be good land.

403
00:39:24,560 --> 00:39:27,640
lt's the finest in the world.
Seeds flourish in it.

404
00:39:27,640 --> 00:39:30,200
The cattle that grow upon it
are fat as elephants.

405
00:39:30,200 --> 00:39:33,080
How do you get it, Mr. McGuire?
ls it there when you step off the boat?

406
00:39:33,080 --> 00:39:35,480
Oh, no. You have to travel
1,000 miles or so.

407
00:39:35,480 --> 00:39:38,560
When you get there, you'll have to
run for the land in a race.

408
00:39:38,560 --> 00:39:40,360
A race?

409
00:39:40,360 --> 00:39:42,280
Don't lose time in Boston.

410
00:39:42,280 --> 00:39:45,360
As soon as you can,
purchase horses, a wagon and supplies.

411
00:39:47,560 --> 00:39:49,600
Have l upset you?

412
00:39:51,040 --> 00:39:53,240
l didn't expect it
to be so complicated.

413
00:39:53,240 --> 00:39:57,080
We're very fortunate. Any difficulty
can be overcome with money.

414
00:39:59,920 --> 00:40:03,280
Excuse me. l'd like
to speak with Mr. McGuire alone.

415
00:40:08,360 --> 00:40:10,880
Mr. McGuire, l do have money...

416
00:40:10,880 --> 00:40:12,800
but it's in the form of spoons.

417
00:40:12,800 --> 00:40:16,040
- Spoons?
- Ancient spoons made of silver.

418
00:40:16,040 --> 00:40:18,720
l'd planned to sell them
when l arrived in Boston.

419
00:40:18,720 --> 00:40:21,600
Well, l can recommend a couple of shops
that will treat you honestly.

420
00:40:21,600 --> 00:40:24,400
Oh, l'm very much obliged to you, sir.

421
00:40:24,400 --> 00:40:27,160
- Pleasure's mine.
- Thank you.

422
00:40:32,560 --> 00:40:35,520
May l ask what are you doing
sitting at my table?

423
00:40:35,520 --> 00:40:37,360
l'm eating your chocolate cake.

424
00:40:39,280 --> 00:40:42,600
l see. And what have you done
with my father's necktie?

425
00:40:44,360 --> 00:40:47,880
l flung it into the sea.
lt was gagging my throat.

426
00:40:49,440 --> 00:40:53,280
You're just upset because everything
l've told you is turning out to be true.

427
00:40:54,600 --> 00:40:57,000
''Cows as fat as elephants.''

428
00:40:57,000 --> 00:40:59,480
l know what that man's after.

429
00:41:02,360 --> 00:41:04,480
l think you should
cover your ankles.

430
00:41:20,880 --> 00:41:22,600
America.

431
00:41:22,600 --> 00:41:24,640
l'm here. l've made it.

432
00:41:25,680 --> 00:41:27,680
l've arrived, Joseph.

433
00:41:32,600 --> 00:41:34,120
l beg your pardon.

434
00:41:38,440 --> 00:41:40,240
United States of America flags!

435
00:41:40,240 --> 00:41:41,680
You're an American today!

436
00:41:44,360 --> 00:41:47,640
Your great friend
Mr. McGuire has vanished.

437
00:41:47,640 --> 00:41:49,360
You want American dollars?

438
00:41:49,360 --> 00:41:51,280
Oh, there he is!
Mr. McGuire!

439
00:41:53,760 --> 00:41:55,200
Over here!

440
00:41:59,240 --> 00:42:00,680
Ah, there you are.

441
00:42:02,880 --> 00:42:04,520
Hey, mister, you lrish?
l can take you to the ward boss.

442
00:42:04,520 --> 00:42:07,760
Need work? Need lodging?
There are people who hate the lrish.

443
00:42:07,760 --> 00:42:11,240
You can't get nothing without the ward
boss. He's the biggest man in Boston.

444
00:42:11,240 --> 00:42:13,640
Go fleece somebody else, boy.

445
00:42:13,640 --> 00:42:16,800
l know the games of these shysters.
Come on, Miss Christie.

446
00:42:16,800 --> 00:42:18,720
l'll find you a suitable hotel.

447
00:42:19,680 --> 00:42:21,120
Cab!

448
00:42:21,120 --> 00:42:23,040
Thank goodness for Mr. McGuire.

449
00:42:23,040 --> 00:42:25,320
Take Miss Christie here
to a decent hotel.

450
00:42:30,600 --> 00:42:34,040
Well, you've certainly upheld
your end of the bargain.

451
00:42:35,320 --> 00:42:36,920
Good luck, Shannon.

452
00:42:36,920 --> 00:42:38,680
Good luck, Joseph.

453
00:42:49,400 --> 00:42:54,280
Need jobs, need lodgings? lf you're
lrish, l'll take you to the ward boss.

454
00:42:55,160 --> 00:42:56,960
Hey, McGuire!

455
00:42:56,960 --> 00:43:00,800
- Yes?
- Welcome back.

456
00:43:05,120 --> 00:43:09,360
Oh, my God! My spoons!
They're taking my spoons!

457
00:43:09,360 --> 00:43:12,600
Joseph, Mr. McGuire stole my spoons!

458
00:43:12,600 --> 00:43:16,080
No, please, they're mine.
He stole them from me.

459
00:43:18,360 --> 00:43:22,480
That dead man stole my spoons.
My bag! They're taking everything!

460
00:43:30,920 --> 00:43:32,640
Now l have nothing.

461
00:43:32,640 --> 00:43:34,680
Come away, Shannon.
We have to go.

462
00:43:34,680 --> 00:43:37,720
l have nothing now.
l have no money.

463
00:43:38,680 --> 00:43:41,480
God is punishing me, Joseph.

464
00:43:41,480 --> 00:43:44,640
l stole those spoons from my mother
the morning l ran away.

465
00:43:44,640 --> 00:43:47,120
Hey, you! Stand still!

466
00:43:47,120 --> 00:43:50,200
- l didn't do nothing!
- Who's this man, the ward boss?

467
00:43:56,040 --> 00:43:58,360
That's him there,
fighting in the fancy clothes.

468
00:43:58,360 --> 00:44:00,840
Mike Kelly, his name is.

469
00:44:00,840 --> 00:44:02,680
- l'll take it.
- Come on!

470
00:44:06,880 --> 00:44:09,080
Shannon, you should
stand back over there.

471
00:44:09,080 --> 00:44:11,200
Don't shield me, Joseph.
lt's only a boxing match.

472
00:44:13,040 --> 00:44:14,080
What?

473
00:44:18,000 --> 00:44:19,280
Sorry, Mike.

474
00:44:20,040 --> 00:44:22,160
Mike isn't happy when he loses.

475
00:44:37,000 --> 00:44:39,680
You distracted me.

476
00:44:40,640 --> 00:44:43,160
You weren't concentrating.

477
00:44:47,280 --> 00:44:50,240
A scrappy Connemara man, huh?

478
00:44:50,240 --> 00:44:52,080
Fresh off the boat.

479
00:44:54,960 --> 00:44:56,080
Follow me.

480
00:44:57,520 --> 00:45:00,120
Not you, woman.
You just cost me part of a tooth.

481
00:45:00,120 --> 00:45:03,080
- lf he gets to go, then l get to go.
- l'm Mike Kelly!

482
00:45:03,080 --> 00:45:06,240
Who is this bit of a snit anyway?
Your wife?

483
00:45:06,240 --> 00:45:09,520
- Certainly not.
- Then who the hell are you, lass?

484
00:45:09,520 --> 00:45:11,640
- She's...
- l'm-

485
00:45:11,640 --> 00:45:13,240
my sister.

486
00:45:14,680 --> 00:45:17,200
- Tell me she isn't a pain in the ass.
- Settle your bets!

487
00:45:17,200 --> 00:45:19,480
''Sister''? Our blood's not even
the same temperature.

488
00:45:21,680 --> 00:45:26,000
These people are my kind of people.

489
00:45:26,960 --> 00:45:30,040
And my kind doesn't like your kind.

490
00:45:32,440 --> 00:45:35,320
ln fact,
they hate everything about you.

491
00:45:41,360 --> 00:45:43,360
Now...

492
00:45:43,360 --> 00:45:45,880
for some reason or other
l'm willing to lie for you.

493
00:45:46,920 --> 00:45:50,200
Or we could tell them you're
a rich Protestant. Might be sporting.

494
00:45:50,200 --> 00:45:51,600
No, Joseph.

495
00:45:53,240 --> 00:45:54,800
My brother.

496
00:45:55,840 --> 00:45:57,080
Good.

497
00:46:04,680 --> 00:46:07,640
- What do you call yourself?
- Joseph Donelly.

498
00:46:07,640 --> 00:46:10,400
Well, Donelly, let's put you
on the road to citizenship.

499
00:46:10,400 --> 00:46:14,240
We'll get you working
and get you voting when the time comes.

500
00:46:15,120 --> 00:46:17,320
See how the system works here, lad?

501
00:46:19,640 --> 00:46:20,880
Stop it!

502
00:46:20,880 --> 00:46:24,040
- Leave me alone!
- 'Twas a lady who took to the street

503
00:46:24,040 --> 00:46:26,320
- Her name was Biddy McMack
- Get away or l'll claw your eyes out!

504
00:46:26,320 --> 00:46:29,400
She makes a handsome living
out of laying on her back

505
00:46:29,400 --> 00:46:32,000
- l said leave me alone!
- Excuse me, Mr. Kelly.

506
00:46:32,000 --> 00:46:34,000
l'm not a wealthy man

507
00:46:34,000 --> 00:46:37,840
But give me a night of paradise
l'll pay you what l can

508
00:46:37,960 --> 00:46:39,280
Get away!

509
00:46:42,080 --> 00:46:44,480
l'll ask you
to leave this lady alone.

510
00:46:44,480 --> 00:46:46,400
Go ahead and ask.

511
00:46:51,760 --> 00:46:53,400
l've no wish to fight you.

512
00:46:53,400 --> 00:46:55,960
He's no wish to fight me.

513
00:46:55,960 --> 00:46:57,680
l'll take him.

514
00:46:57,680 --> 00:46:59,920
No, he's mine.

515
00:46:59,920 --> 00:47:01,720
He's mine alone.

516
00:47:05,840 --> 00:47:07,200
Kill him, Joseph!

517
00:47:30,400 --> 00:47:31,760
Well, now.

518
00:47:32,600 --> 00:47:35,880
You knocked the piss out of the man
who knocked the piss out of me.

519
00:47:35,880 --> 00:47:37,880
l'm not sure
how l feel about that.

520
00:47:38,840 --> 00:47:40,960
- Dermody.
- Yes, sir, Mr. Kelly.

521
00:47:40,960 --> 00:47:42,680
Time to make the rounds.

522
00:47:42,680 --> 00:47:45,560
We'll take this scrapper
and the girl...

523
00:47:45,560 --> 00:47:47,840
and lodge them at Molly Kay's.

524
00:47:47,840 --> 00:47:49,760
- Grab the luggage.
- Yes, sir.

525
00:47:50,840 --> 00:47:52,160
Come on.

526
00:47:53,880 --> 00:47:57,440
Hey, Pete. Get a match going
these fellows can bet on. l'll be back.

527
00:47:58,120 --> 00:47:59,840
Hey, Mike, how are you doing?

528
00:47:59,840 --> 00:48:02,520
All depends, huh?
Good to see you lads.

529
00:48:02,520 --> 00:48:04,640
- This is it. Here we are.
- Good day to you, Mr. Kelly!

530
00:48:08,560 --> 00:48:11,720
- Molly!
- lt's as unpleasant for me as for you.

531
00:48:11,720 --> 00:48:14,520
