Molly, need a room.

532
00:48:14,520 --> 00:48:17,960
You're in luck.
We had a suicide just this morning.

533
00:48:21,120 --> 00:48:23,520
- Hello, Bridget. How are you?
- Hello, Mike.

534
00:48:23,520 --> 00:48:26,400
Ah, yes.
Any gentlemen up here, girls?

535
00:48:26,400 --> 00:48:27,640
No, not here, Mike.

536
00:48:27,640 --> 00:48:31,760
- Make an announcement, Dermody.
- Ward boss!

537
00:48:31,760 --> 00:48:34,560
- l'd give you another year.
- You're not campaigning, Mike.

538
00:48:34,560 --> 00:48:37,240
Relax, Molly. Politics is
more important to these men than sex.

539
00:48:37,240 --> 00:48:39,160
And l'm the Virgin Mary.

540
00:48:39,160 --> 00:48:41,480
- God forgive you, Molly.
- Not likely, Mike.

541
00:48:41,480 --> 00:48:43,080
Come on.

542
00:48:43,080 --> 00:48:46,280
ls that Jimmy Dunne l see?
l was chatting with your wife today.

543
00:48:46,280 --> 00:48:48,960
Don't tell my wife, Mike.

544
00:48:48,960 --> 00:48:53,280
And here's the bath, but don't linger
in it too long. lt's the only one.

545
00:48:54,120 --> 00:48:57,080
Gentlemen,
button up your trousers.

546
00:49:01,880 --> 00:49:03,600
This is your room here.

547
00:49:06,880 --> 00:49:08,240
Ours?

548
00:49:08,240 --> 00:49:10,320
You're not suggesting
that we share this room, l hope.

549
00:49:11,280 --> 00:49:12,920
l don't care what you do in it...

550
00:49:12,920 --> 00:49:15,880
as long as you pay me
a dollar a week.

551
00:49:17,640 --> 00:49:19,840
There must be some mistake.
We need two rooms.

552
00:49:19,840 --> 00:49:22,240
- l've only got the one.
- That's not good enough.

553
00:49:22,240 --> 00:49:25,600
- Mike, what have you sent me here?
- You're not listening to me.

554
00:49:25,600 --> 00:49:28,760
The room is fine,
and we'll take it gratefully.

555
00:49:28,760 --> 00:49:30,560
As you know,
election time is coming up-

556
00:49:33,080 --> 00:49:35,920
Your sister was spoilt, l'd say.

557
00:49:35,920 --> 00:49:37,480
Here for your support.

558
00:49:37,480 --> 00:49:41,200
l'm sure you've noticed
all these ltalians taking lrish jobs.

559
00:49:41,200 --> 00:49:45,320
No ltalians are gonna run this town
as long as Mike Kelly's in charge.

560
00:50:17,280 --> 00:50:19,080
Shannon, are you awake?

561
00:50:19,960 --> 00:50:21,800
No, l'm sound asleep.

562
00:50:22,840 --> 00:50:25,520
l think l like America.

563
00:50:27,040 --> 00:50:29,160
- Do you, now?
- Aye.

564
00:50:30,240 --> 00:50:33,960
We've only been here a day.
Look at the welcome we've got.

565
00:50:33,960 --> 00:50:35,480
Would you like a room?
Here you go.

566
00:50:36,760 --> 00:50:40,080
Would you like a job?
Why, here you go.

567
00:50:40,080 --> 00:50:43,080
How about some land?

568
00:50:43,080 --> 00:50:44,880
Well, get a horse,
and help yourself.

569
00:50:45,960 --> 00:50:48,520
So, now you believe me
about the land, do you?

570
00:50:49,400 --> 00:50:51,880
lf they're throwing it away,
l wouldn't mind a piece of it.

571
00:50:58,720 --> 00:51:02,080
Maybe this is my destiny.

572
00:51:03,040 --> 00:51:07,640
On his deathbed, my father told me
he'd be watching me from up above.

573
00:51:09,360 --> 00:51:13,200
l wonder now if his spirit
might be near, guiding me along.

574
00:51:13,360 --> 00:51:16,640
lf he bumps into Mr. McGuire up there,
tell him l want my spoons back.

575
00:51:18,000 --> 00:51:20,000
lmagine me...

576
00:51:20,000 --> 00:51:23,080
Joseph Donelly,
standing on my own plot of land.

577
00:51:25,000 --> 00:51:27,760
What would l plant, l wonder?

578
00:51:27,760 --> 00:51:31,120
Oats, corn, potatoes-

579
00:51:31,120 --> 00:51:34,000
Oh, God, no, not potatoes.

580
00:51:34,000 --> 00:51:35,640
Maybe wheat.

581
00:51:36,680 --> 00:51:38,040
Wheat.

582
00:51:39,080 --> 00:51:41,280
Oh, Shannon...

583
00:51:41,280 --> 00:51:43,960
l'm dreaming of it now.

584
00:51:43,960 --> 00:51:47,720
Great fields of wheat
as far as the eye can see.

585
00:51:47,720 --> 00:51:51,360
Oklahoma land was my idea,
you blathering fool!

586
00:51:51,360 --> 00:51:53,360
''Maybe this is my destiny.''

587
00:51:53,360 --> 00:51:55,880
lf it weren't for me, farm boy,
you wouldn't even be here!

588
00:51:55,880 --> 00:51:58,920
Well, if it weren't for me,
Miss High and Mighty...

589
00:51:58,920 --> 00:52:01,440
you'd have died
outside in the street.

590
00:52:06,400 --> 00:52:08,600
Give me back my pillow.

591
00:52:10,520 --> 00:52:12,440
Not in a hundred years.

592
00:52:28,000 --> 00:52:30,480
This book is irritating me.

593
00:52:47,440 --> 00:52:49,960
Do you actually think
you're fooling me, Daniel?

594
00:52:56,280 --> 00:52:59,920
Would you prefer l proclaim
my independence and drink in the open?

595
00:53:02,600 --> 00:53:04,520
l like the system we've got.

596
00:53:08,840 --> 00:53:11,040
How could she be so cruel?

597
00:53:11,040 --> 00:53:13,440
Not to send us any word.

598
00:53:18,040 --> 00:53:19,600
She's in America, Nora.

599
00:53:26,480 --> 00:53:29,160
She's been writing to me
for some time now.

600
00:53:34,080 --> 00:53:36,080
You hid these from me?

601
00:53:37,720 --> 00:53:40,960
At Shannon's request.

602
00:53:40,960 --> 00:53:43,360
Read them now...

603
00:53:43,360 --> 00:53:45,480
though they may not
bring you comfort.

604
00:53:56,240 --> 00:53:59,280
- Death to the landlord!
- Burn the house to the ground!

605
00:53:59,280 --> 00:54:01,800
Burn it down!

606
00:54:03,400 --> 00:54:05,320
Captain Moonlight!

607
00:54:11,200 --> 00:54:13,120
Get out of the house, Nora!

608
00:54:13,120 --> 00:54:16,920
- Oh, the letters!
- Leave the letters alone, Nora!

609
00:54:19,440 --> 00:54:21,840
Burn down every last one of them!

610
00:54:25,560 --> 00:54:27,680
Come with me.

611
00:54:27,680 --> 00:54:29,880
Stephen!
We're over here!

612
00:54:29,880 --> 00:54:31,800
Quickly. This way.

613
00:54:55,000 --> 00:54:57,520
All of your life,
collected and destroyed.

614
00:55:01,840 --> 00:55:04,120
l'm truly sorry
for your loss.

615
00:55:07,080 --> 00:55:11,320
Does this mean we're finished?
Are we impoverished now?

616
00:55:11,320 --> 00:55:15,160
No, sir. You still have your land
and your holdings.

617
00:55:23,480 --> 00:55:26,200
This is no longer the lreland
of my birth.

618
00:55:31,280 --> 00:55:33,840
Our daughter's fallen
into perilous ruin, Daniel.

619
00:55:33,840 --> 00:55:36,040
- We must go to her now.
- Shannon?

620
00:55:40,080 --> 00:55:42,280
She's-

621
00:55:42,280 --> 00:55:44,680
She's been in Boston
these many months.

622
00:55:49,600 --> 00:55:51,480
Then we shall find her there.

623
00:55:52,160 --> 00:55:54,480
You over there, keep working.

624
00:55:54,480 --> 00:55:56,400
lf you don't work,
you don't get paid.

625
00:55:56,400 --> 00:55:58,600
Get those chickens plucked.

626
00:56:07,240 --> 00:56:09,040
Get to work.

627
00:56:16,800 --> 00:56:19,200
l think the prettiest girl
in this factory...

628
00:56:19,200 --> 00:56:23,040
one with the prettiest eyes and the
prettiest red hair is Joseph's sister.

629
00:56:23,040 --> 00:56:25,080
lf you don't mind my saying so.

630
00:56:25,080 --> 00:56:27,160
You can say what you like, lad.

631
00:56:27,160 --> 00:56:31,280
But l warn you,
that redhead has a bite that stings.

632
00:56:33,680 --> 00:56:35,600
Get to work.

633
00:56:35,600 --> 00:56:37,720
Get your filthy hands off me,
you ugly animal.

634
00:56:42,120 --> 00:56:43,880
That'll cost you a day's wage.

635
00:56:47,880 --> 00:56:51,040
Go ahead.
lnsult me again.

636
00:56:58,040 --> 00:56:59,120
Pig.

637
00:57:02,680 --> 00:57:04,280
There goes tomorrow.

638
00:57:06,200 --> 00:57:07,760
Done?

639
00:57:19,360 --> 00:57:23,480
Take Friday as well, you spineless
little fraction of a man.

640
00:57:25,600 --> 00:57:27,960
Bite, lads. Bite.

641
00:57:47,840 --> 00:57:49,960
What are you looking at?

642
00:57:52,800 --> 00:57:56,160
l'm just trying to figure out
what you're doing there.

643
00:57:56,160 --> 00:57:58,760
lt's obvious what l'm doing.
l'm cleaning my clothes.

644
00:57:58,760 --> 00:58:01,080
l see.

645
00:58:01,080 --> 00:58:04,520
Do you ever wonder
why it takes you so long?

646
00:58:04,520 --> 00:58:06,360
My clothes, if you notice,
if you look about...

647
00:58:06,360 --> 00:58:10,160
are washed and hung- done.

648
00:58:11,920 --> 00:58:14,680
Your talent astounds me, Joseph.

649
00:58:16,200 --> 00:58:18,920
Move over.
Move over.

650
00:58:21,680 --> 00:58:24,000
lf you want to clean your clothes,
you have to get your hands wet.

651
00:58:24,000 --> 00:58:27,640
First, you place the board
like so.

652
00:58:27,640 --> 00:58:31,960
You take the soap in your right hand,
the clothes in the left.

653
00:58:31,960 --> 00:58:34,440
Then you brush the soap
across the clothes twice.

654
00:58:34,440 --> 00:58:36,440
Like so.

655
00:58:36,440 --> 00:58:38,280
Then you plunge and scrub.

656
00:58:38,280 --> 00:58:40,400
You plunge and scrub.

657
00:58:44,600 --> 00:58:46,440
And plunge and scrub and lift.

658
00:58:48,640 --> 00:58:52,480
And if it's still not clean,
well, then you go again.

659
00:58:52,560 --> 00:58:54,760
You plunge and scrub.

660
00:58:55,520 --> 00:58:58,240
You keep on plunging and scrubbing...

661
00:58:58,240 --> 00:59:02,560
till all your plunging and scrubbing
is done.

662
00:59:10,120 --> 00:59:12,600
Thirty, forty...

663
00:59:12,600 --> 00:59:16,920
forty-five-
forty-five, fifty.

664
00:59:16,920 --> 00:59:19,600
You could be a banker, Joseph,
with your ability to count.

665
00:59:19,600 --> 00:59:22,200
Oh, a compliment.

666
00:59:23,240 --> 00:59:25,760
Thank you, Shannon.

667
00:59:25,760 --> 00:59:28,240
Don't suppose you've calculated
what the journey will cost.

668
00:59:29,400 --> 00:59:32,280
lf l barter, l can get a buckboard
for under 25.

669
00:59:32,280 --> 00:59:34,480
lt's the harness that's costly.

670
00:59:34,480 --> 00:59:37,360
Bit, frame-

671
00:59:40,120 --> 00:59:43,680
Frame, collar, reins.

672
00:59:43,680 --> 00:59:46,760
Oh. Very impressive.

673
00:59:46,760 --> 00:59:50,480
How much have you saved?

674
00:59:52,320 --> 00:59:54,320
Are you still praying you'll
make it to the Oklahoma land race?

675
00:59:54,320 --> 00:59:57,680
- l'll get there.
- Ha! What a corker.

676
00:59:59,200 --> 01:00:01,240
You're a corker, Shannon.

677
01:00:02,080 --> 01:00:04,320
Why don't you go back home to lreland?
Write to your parents for money.

678
01:00:04,320 --> 01:00:07,760
They'll forgive you
for your petty foolishness.

679
01:00:10,840 --> 01:00:15,520
America may not be exactly
what l thought it would be, but...

680
01:00:15,520 --> 01:00:17,520
if l went back to lreland,
l wouldn't-

681
01:00:18,800 --> 01:00:21,200
What?

682
01:00:21,200 --> 01:00:23,280
Wouldn't what?

683
01:00:23,280 --> 01:00:25,480
l said l'll get there,
and l'll get there- by myself.

684
01:00:26,160 --> 01:00:28,560
Well, you need supplies.

685
01:00:28,560 --> 01:00:32,960
- Of course. Food, clothes-
- Ammunition, gun.

686
01:00:32,960 --> 01:00:36,440
Whenever l think of guns,
l remember Stephen Chase.

687
01:00:39,320 --> 01:00:42,480
You're lucky to be rid
of that piss-headed snob.

688
01:00:42,480 --> 01:00:47,160
Oh, he wasn't so bad.
You didn't know him as well as l did.

689
01:00:47,160 --> 01:00:49,840
l knew him well enough.

690
01:00:49,840 --> 01:00:52,160
Me, he adored.

691
01:00:52,160 --> 01:00:54,280
He worshiped me.

692
01:00:54,280 --> 01:00:56,360
There wasn't a puddle of mud
he didn't lay his coat upon...

693
01:00:56,360 --> 01:00:58,200
for me to walk across.

694
01:01:08,840 --> 01:01:13,440
- Are you facing east?
- Aye. Facing east.

695
01:01:14,520 --> 01:01:16,440
All right.

696
01:01:18,640 --> 01:01:20,560
Almost ready.

697
01:01:20,560 --> 01:01:22,480
Thanks be to Jesus.

698
01:01:23,720 --> 01:01:25,520
Light.

699
01:01:34,080 --> 01:01:35,200
l'm in.

700
01:01:46,360 --> 01:01:47,960
Good night, Shannon.

701
01:02:01,960 --> 01:02:03,520
What?

702
01:02:07,520 --> 01:02:09,840
Am l beautiful at all?

703
01:02:24,240 --> 01:02:28,440
l've never seen anything like you
in all my living life.

704
01:02:30,640 --> 01:02:32,360
Good.

705
01:02:52,440 --> 01:02:55,960
Let's have another boxing match.
We need another challenger.

706
01:02:55,960 --> 01:02:59,720
This man has not been defeated tonight.
Will anyone box him?

707
01:02:59,720 --> 01:03:02,320
Any challengers to-
Oh, sir, you can beat him.

708
01:03:02,320 --> 01:03:04,680
- You've got the face of a winner.
- l'll fight him.

709
01:03:10,280 --> 01:03:12,760
No! No, no, no, no!

710
01:03:12,760 --> 01:03:14,680
Joseph, there's rules
in this club.

711
01:03:14,680 --> 01:03:17,360
Toe the line and all that.
You got to wait until l signal.

712
01:03:23,800 --> 01:03:25,720
Toe the line, gentlemen.

713
01:03:25,720 --> 01:03:28,880
No kicking, no biting, no gouging.

714
01:03:31,160 --> 01:03:34,520
- Fight me here, farmer!
- Put your foot on the line.

715
01:03:36,440 --> 01:03:39,320
- Right.
- Toe the line. Toe the line.

716
01:03:39,320 --> 01:03:41,160
- Get away.
- Put your toe on the line.

717
01:03:44,960 --> 01:03:48,800
- Come on. You're yellow!
- Come on!

718
01:03:51,880 --> 01:03:53,240
Go on, scrapper!

719
01:04:09,640 --> 01:04:11,360
Stop it.
You've won, Joseph. Stop it.

720
01:04:12,520 --> 01:04:15,760
What a fight!
l knew you had it in you.

721
01:04:15,760 --> 01:04:18,840
Girls, get up the burly-cue.

722
01:04:18,840 --> 01:04:21,440
- What do you call yourself again?
- Joseph. Joseph Donelly.

723
01:04:21,440 --> 01:04:24,760
That's right. You clobbered
that fella's brains out, lad.

724
01:04:24,760 --> 01:04:27,000
l discovered this fella
fresh off the boat.

725
01:04:28,800 --> 01:04:32,360
Gordon, get this scrapper
something to smoke.

726
01:04:35,520 --> 01:04:37,040
Who's your boy there, Kelly?

727
01:04:38,960 --> 01:04:40,880
A newfangled style of fighting
he's got there.

728
01:04:40,880 --> 01:04:42,920
He's slippery, all right.

729
01:04:42,920 --> 01:04:45,320
Shake hands with Mr. D'Arcy Bourke,
member of the city council.

730
01:04:47,040 --> 01:04:49,600
l'll shake your hand, Mr. Bourke,
but l'm not in a friendly mood.

731
01:04:49,600 --> 01:04:52,320
l came here to fight.
There's fight left in me yet.

732
01:04:52,320 --> 01:04:54,520
He's a lively one, Kelly.

733
01:04:55,960 --> 01:04:57,880
Would you box an ltalian
if l scared one up?

734
01:04:59,320 --> 01:05:01,400
l'll box any man
you put in front of me.

735
01:05:01,400 --> 01:05:03,320
Mike! Mike! Mike!

736
01:05:03,320 --> 01:05:06,880
Jesus Christ, Dermody.
When's your voice gonna change?

737
01:05:06,880 --> 01:05:08,720
- We've got another pug.
- Bring him on.

738
01:05:08,720 --> 01:05:10,040
And l'll put money on you.

739
01:05:10,720 --> 01:05:13,120
Place your bets, gentlemen.

740
01:05:13,120 --> 01:05:16,200
The boy's got an appetite, Kelly.

741
01:05:16,200 --> 01:05:18,000
Toe the line, gentlemen.

742
01:05:34,680 --> 01:05:37,760
lt's nothing!
l'm feeling grand tonight.

743
01:05:39,760 --> 01:05:42,440
Steady now, you rogue.

744
01:05:46,760 --> 01:05:50,600
- What happened?
- Help me get him into bed.

745
01:05:50,600 --> 01:05:53,280
Joseph, you're covered in blood.
What happened to you?

746
01:05:53,280 --> 01:05:57,520
He's been prize fighting,
but he'll survive.

747
01:05:57,520 --> 01:06:01,240
He had a charge of gunpowder in him
that needed to go off.

748
01:06:01,240 --> 01:06:03,360
And who might you be?

749
01:06:03,360 --> 01:06:05,960
l'm Grace.
l work at the social club.

750
01:06:05,960 --> 01:06:08,720
l did well tonight, didn't l?

751
01:06:10,960 --> 01:06:14,280
You beat 'em all.
But don't talk now.

752
01:06:17,080 --> 01:06:19,200
Get some sleep.

753
01:06:23,800 --> 01:06:25,600
l need to talk to you.

754
