01:28:04,960 --> 01:28:07,640
We can't keep wandering like this.

994
01:28:07,640 --> 01:28:09,200
l know.

995
01:28:11,680 --> 01:28:13,600
lt's been so long.

996
01:28:13,600 --> 01:28:16,560
Too many days.
We can't keep doing this.

997
01:28:18,000 --> 01:28:20,400
l think this house is empty.

998
01:28:39,480 --> 01:28:41,400
Look.

999
01:28:42,640 --> 01:28:45,440
- A tree.
- Look! Food!

1000
01:28:46,480 --> 01:28:49,000
There's food here.

1001
01:29:15,640 --> 01:29:17,480
Joseph, look at us.

1002
01:29:22,160 --> 01:29:24,960
l never thought
it would turn out like this.

1003
01:29:26,960 --> 01:29:29,160
And we know
there's sweeter land.

1004
01:29:41,840 --> 01:29:44,120
Sit down.

1005
01:29:44,120 --> 01:29:46,040
Sit down at this beautiful table.

1006
01:29:46,040 --> 01:29:49,000
No. We can't. We're burglars.

1007
01:29:49,000 --> 01:29:53,320
Please. Please.
l want you to pretend.

1008
01:29:54,480 --> 01:29:56,400
Sit down.
l'll serve you.

1009
01:29:58,040 --> 01:30:01,600
Tonight l want you to dine.

1010
01:30:28,640 --> 01:30:32,480
No, Joseph. Don't serve me.
Just sit down.

1011
01:30:32,560 --> 01:30:34,280
Sit down with me.

1012
01:30:35,520 --> 01:30:38,320
Let's pretend...

1013
01:30:38,320 --> 01:30:40,520
that this house is ours.

1014
01:30:43,200 --> 01:30:45,800
That you're my husband...

1015
01:30:45,800 --> 01:30:47,600
and l'm your wife.

1016
01:30:53,360 --> 01:30:55,200
Sit down.

1017
01:31:05,840 --> 01:31:09,400
Did you ever wonder what that land
you dreamed of looked like?

1018
01:31:11,400 --> 01:31:14,280
- Aye.
- Mine-

1019
01:31:14,280 --> 01:31:17,440
Mine was a green pasture
with tall grass...

1020
01:31:17,440 --> 01:31:19,360
that rolled just a little bit.

1021
01:31:19,360 --> 01:31:21,560
Mine had a stream
running through it.

1022
01:31:23,000 --> 01:31:25,120
Perhaps some trees.

1023
01:31:25,120 --> 01:31:27,040
Rich, dark soil.

1024
01:31:28,280 --> 01:31:30,480
No rocks to pick out of the ground.

1025
01:31:31,920 --> 01:31:34,880
Green pasture and a stream.

1026
01:31:34,880 --> 01:31:36,920
They would complement
each other, no?

1027
01:31:38,160 --> 01:31:41,040
They would.

1028
01:31:41,040 --> 01:31:43,800
The one, in fact...

1029
01:31:43,800 --> 01:31:45,640
depends upon the other.

1030
01:31:47,760 --> 01:31:50,520
Pretend...

1031
01:31:50,520 --> 01:31:52,560
you love me.

1032
01:31:53,320 --> 01:31:55,120
l'll pretend l love you.

1033
01:31:57,920 --> 01:32:00,320
l'll pretend l love you too.

1034
01:32:36,760 --> 01:32:38,760
- What was that?
- Who's there?

1035
01:32:48,760 --> 01:32:50,760
Get the hell out of my house!

1036
01:32:59,480 --> 01:33:02,160
Police! Police!

1037
01:33:02,160 --> 01:33:04,080
Get the police!

1038
01:33:18,080 --> 01:33:19,160
Help!

1039
01:33:21,840 --> 01:33:25,480
This girl needs help!
Will you let us in?

1040
01:33:25,480 --> 01:33:27,400
This-

1041
01:33:33,720 --> 01:33:36,600
ls this the Christies'?

1042
01:33:41,960 --> 01:33:44,280
Just let us in.

1043
01:33:52,320 --> 01:33:54,520
- Quickly, fetch a doctor.
- Yes, sir.

1044
01:33:55,280 --> 01:33:58,960
Step aside. You'll infect her
with your filthy hands.

1045
01:33:58,960 --> 01:34:01,640
What did you expect?
That you could climb to her station?

1046
01:34:03,640 --> 01:34:06,720
- Gunshot!
- Aye.

1047
01:34:11,200 --> 01:34:13,800
God, look at her.

1048
01:34:14,960 --> 01:34:17,760
- Will she be all right?
- She will now.

1049
01:34:18,800 --> 01:34:20,800
The wound is in the shoulder.
l have to clean it.

1050
01:34:47,960 --> 01:34:50,360
Shannon, l-

1051
01:34:55,920 --> 01:34:58,480
You're safe now...

1052
01:34:58,480 --> 01:35:00,320
in this house.

1053
01:35:04,080 --> 01:35:06,080
You're gonna be fine.

1054
01:35:19,880 --> 01:35:21,240
Take care of her.

1055
01:35:41,360 --> 01:35:44,640
Mr. Christie, here's the doctor.

1056
01:35:44,640 --> 01:35:47,120
- Something terrible has happened.
- What is it, Doctor?

1057
01:35:47,120 --> 01:35:49,440
- Your daughter, Mr. Christie.
- Shannon? She's here?

1058
01:35:49,440 --> 01:35:51,240
What's happened to her?

1059
01:36:23,000 --> 01:36:26,840
All right, she's all clear!
Let's get the mud cleaned out.

1060
01:36:26,920 --> 01:36:30,480
Hey, mick, after you drop that tile,
let's get after these rocks.

1061
01:36:30,480 --> 01:36:35,560
Come on! Let's get some goddamn work
done here. Fill up that wheel barrow.

1062
01:36:40,240 --> 01:36:42,360
Come on, fill it up.
Fill it up.

1063
01:37:19,960 --> 01:37:23,600
Move it! Hey!
Fire in the hole!

1064
01:37:26,200 --> 01:37:29,760
Come on, boys, find yourself some cover.
We got fire in the hole!

1065
01:37:29,760 --> 01:37:32,720
Hey, you!
Fire in the hole!

1066
01:38:13,840 --> 01:38:15,280
Water!

1067
01:38:16,240 --> 01:38:18,160
Anybody need water?

1068
01:38:19,240 --> 01:38:21,040
Water?

1069
01:38:23,440 --> 01:38:27,960
Look at that. All them wagons headed
for the Oklahoma Territory.

1070
01:38:28,800 --> 01:38:31,200
l'd be going wit them
if l was as young as you.

1071
01:38:31,200 --> 01:38:33,040
Doesn't interest me.

1072
01:38:51,640 --> 01:38:53,840
l had a woman once.

1073
01:38:53,840 --> 01:38:56,360
But she didn't want me
'cause l had no money.

1074
01:38:56,360 --> 01:39:00,080
That's America.
Unless you're rich, you're nobody.

1075
01:39:00,080 --> 01:39:03,160
l should never have come
to this place.

1076
01:39:03,160 --> 01:39:07,360
Forget the women, boys.
You got a job of work ahead of you.

1077
01:39:30,960 --> 01:39:34,240
Da, is that you?

1078
01:39:35,280 --> 01:39:39,120
Oh, you look like you're
not doing too well, my boy.

1079
01:39:39,120 --> 01:39:41,040
l missed you, Da.

1080
01:39:43,720 --> 01:39:46,480
A man is nothing
without land, they say.

1081
01:39:49,280 --> 01:39:53,120
Land is a man's own soul.

1082
01:39:56,560 --> 01:39:58,480
l'll work my own land someday.

1083
01:39:59,360 --> 01:40:04,320
lf you manage it, by God,
your old Da...

1084
01:40:04,320 --> 01:40:08,000
will be smiling down on you
from heaven above.

1085
01:40:12,760 --> 01:40:16,320
Stay where you are, boys.
We're just stopping for water.

1086
01:40:16,320 --> 01:40:18,240
Oh, look.
lt's the pioneers.

1087
01:40:19,600 --> 01:40:23,320
They go to Oklahoma, l think...

1088
01:40:23,320 --> 01:40:25,440
for the free land.

1089
01:40:27,840 --> 01:40:31,200
They're just wasting time.
There ain't enough land to go around.

1090
01:40:34,640 --> 01:40:37,040
One in a hundred
will stake a claim.

1091
01:40:37,040 --> 01:40:38,960
The rest of 'em-

1092
01:40:38,960 --> 01:40:41,560
they just dreaming.

1093
01:40:41,560 --> 01:40:43,640
Think they gonna get
some free land.

1094
01:40:52,960 --> 01:40:54,000
Hey, lrish!

1095
01:40:56,320 --> 01:40:58,720
Hey, mick, where do you think
you're going?

1096
01:40:58,720 --> 01:41:00,720
l was on the wrong road!

1097
01:42:11,320 --> 01:42:14,280
There now!
Coming through!

1098
01:42:16,880 --> 01:42:19,840
- Coming through!
- Farmers, ranchers, homesteaders!

1099
01:42:19,840 --> 01:42:21,760
This well-driller is an example...

1100
01:42:21,760 --> 01:42:24,560
of modern American industry
at its finest.

1101
01:42:24,560 --> 01:42:28,000
Come up and have a look.
lt's not gonna bite. lt's just modern.

1102
01:42:28,000 --> 01:42:30,400
You may find land tomorrow,
but you won't survive...

1103
01:42:30,400 --> 01:42:32,400
in the wilderness,
not without water.

1104
01:42:34,240 --> 01:42:36,160
''Land Office''

1105
01:42:41,160 --> 01:42:44,400
Folks, each quarter section
is marked.

1106
01:42:44,400 --> 01:42:50,160
You run for land, remove the marker
and drive in your own stake.

1107
01:42:50,160 --> 01:42:53,400
The race begins tomorrow at noon.

1108
01:42:53,400 --> 01:42:56,600
Again, each quarter section is marked.

1109
01:42:56,600 --> 01:43:00,400
- You run for land-
- Where can l get a horse?

1110
01:43:02,320 --> 01:43:04,640
Well, you're a little late,
cowboy.

1111
01:43:04,640 --> 01:43:06,840
Pickings are slim.

1112
01:43:06,840 --> 01:43:11,240
Now, this here horse is broke.

1113
01:43:11,240 --> 01:43:14,800
That horse there-
green broke.

1114
01:43:14,800 --> 01:43:16,920
Know the difference?

1115
01:43:16,920 --> 01:43:18,840
Think l can see it.

1116
01:43:20,160 --> 01:43:23,920
A broke horse
is a dependable horse.

1117
01:43:23,920 --> 01:43:27,160
A green broke horse-
he's faster.

1118
01:43:28,720 --> 01:43:31,000
That sounds good.
The faster, the better.

1119
01:43:31,680 --> 01:43:33,320
No telling what he'll do though.

1120
01:43:33,320 --> 01:43:36,280
Hell, you could end up in Canada
on that green broke son of a bitch.

1121
01:43:37,240 --> 01:43:38,480
Stand back!

1122
01:43:44,640 --> 01:43:47,800
l think l'll take
the dependable horse.

1123
01:43:47,800 --> 01:43:49,040
l would.

1124
01:43:49,040 --> 01:43:51,720
You go out and get you a good piece
of land tomorrow now, Joseph.

1125
01:43:51,720 --> 01:43:53,080
Thank you, Ralph.

1126
01:44:23,560 --> 01:44:26,040
l'm cursed.

1127
01:44:26,040 --> 01:44:28,160
Oh, Lord, l'm cursed.

1128
01:44:38,920 --> 01:44:41,600
Mother, the clothes will never come
clean if you don't get your hands wet.

1129
01:44:43,800 --> 01:44:47,160
There's no order
in this godforsaken place.

1130
01:44:47,160 --> 01:44:51,960
Here. Take the soap
and you plunge and scrub.

1131
01:44:51,960 --> 01:44:54,080
- ''Plunge and scrub''?
- Like so.

1132
01:44:57,600 --> 01:44:59,800
Nora!

1133
01:44:59,800 --> 01:45:01,240
l've been shot.

1134
01:45:01,240 --> 01:45:02,680
Shot?

1135
01:45:02,680 --> 01:45:05,280
Well, shot at, anyway...

1136
01:45:05,280 --> 01:45:07,480
by the cavalry.

1137
01:45:07,480 --> 01:45:11,320
We crossed the starting line
and we broke the law.

1138
01:45:11,520 --> 01:45:14,600
Daniel Christie, l will not have you
riding tomorrow...

1139
01:45:14,600 --> 01:45:17,360
in that vulgarity of a race.

1140
01:45:17,360 --> 01:45:20,360
The wild west suits me, Nora.

1141
01:45:20,360 --> 01:45:22,360
There's no telling what l might do.

1142
01:45:29,360 --> 01:45:32,120
Shannon, l found it!

1143
01:45:32,120 --> 01:45:35,680
Twenty miles straight west of here.
lt's paradise itself.

1144
01:45:35,680 --> 01:45:38,760
You will love it.
The earth is dry and dusty here...

1145
01:45:38,760 --> 01:45:41,840
but where we'll live
there's a winding stream...

1146
01:45:41,840 --> 01:45:45,560
and the grass on the gentle hills
around it grows high and rich and green.

1147
01:45:47,200 --> 01:45:49,600
lt's the plot of land
you've dreamed of.

1148
01:45:52,200 --> 01:45:54,000
Excuse me, Stephen.

1149
01:45:56,600 --> 01:45:59,840
- Are you cross with me?
- Of course l am.

1150
01:45:59,840 --> 01:46:01,880
We were doing this together,
l thought.

1151
01:46:01,880 --> 01:46:04,360
l couldn't take you with me today.
lt was too dangerous.

1152
01:46:04,360 --> 01:46:06,360
l don't mind a little danger
now and then.

1153
01:46:06,360 --> 01:46:08,960
Stop this childishness.

1154
01:46:08,960 --> 01:46:12,600
Are we not here, your parents and l,
because you wanted this?

1155
01:46:12,600 --> 01:46:16,440
Tomorrow we'll ride as one,
together, side by side.

1156
01:46:16,440 --> 01:46:18,840
We'll claim our land,
and then we'll marry...

1157
01:46:18,840 --> 01:46:21,240
and finally settle down.

1158
01:46:25,840 --> 01:46:27,840
You do want to settle down,
don't you, Shannon?

1159
01:46:30,640 --> 01:46:32,560
Yes.

1160
01:46:32,560 --> 01:46:34,960
Yes, l want to settle down.

1161
01:46:37,080 --> 01:46:40,320
There now. That's better.

1162
01:46:43,000 --> 01:46:44,840
l hate to see you angry.

1163
01:46:46,760 --> 01:46:48,880
lt isn't your nature to be so.

1164
01:46:59,600 --> 01:47:01,440
Hello, Shannon.

1165
01:47:14,760 --> 01:47:19,080
l wondered if l'd see you here.
l suspected that l might.

1166
01:47:20,400 --> 01:47:24,160
That's right. l saw you living
back in Boston all this while.

1167
01:47:30,560 --> 01:47:32,960
You look well. Well.

1168
01:47:34,800 --> 01:47:36,640
l'm here with my family.

1169
01:47:36,640 --> 01:47:39,480
We came by train.

1170
01:47:39,480 --> 01:47:40,840
l came by train myself.

1171
01:47:42,280 --> 01:47:45,720
You'll be running in the race
tomorrow, l presume.

1172
01:47:45,720 --> 01:47:49,000
l always said l'd get my land.

1173
01:47:49,000 --> 01:47:51,880
l even bought a horse.
A fine horse.

1174
01:48:05,120 --> 01:48:06,640
Well-

1175
01:48:08,360 --> 01:48:10,280
Time takes care of everything,
doesn't it?

1176
01:48:13,240 --> 01:48:15,840
Everything's worked out...

1177
01:48:15,840 --> 01:48:18,440
as it should have.

1178
01:48:18,440 --> 01:48:19,480
Don't you agree?

1179
01:48:25,160 --> 01:48:26,200
Yeah.

1180
01:48:29,760 --> 01:48:31,000
Good luck tomorrow, Joseph.

1181
01:48:31,000 --> 01:48:32,440
Aye.

1182
01:48:33,760 --> 01:48:36,960
Best of luck to you, Shannon.

1183
01:48:52,960 --> 01:48:54,000
Shannon Christie!

1184
01:48:57,280 --> 01:48:59,080
You never gave up.

1185
01:49:00,640 --> 01:49:03,600
You knew what you wanted
back in lreland.

1186
01:49:03,600 --> 01:49:06,400
And look at ya.
Here ya are.

1187
01:49:12,040 --> 01:49:13,960
You're a corker, Shannon.

1188
01:49:15,880 --> 01:49:17,720
What a corker you are.

1189
01:49:44,640 --> 01:49:46,960
Beautiful country, isn't it, boy?

1190
01:49:48,280 --> 01:49:51,480
l found the perfect piece of land
for Shannon and me.

1191
01:49:51,480 --> 01:49:53,960
Almost a picture
of what she described.

1192
01:49:53,960 --> 01:49:56,440
The land of her dreams.

1193
01:49:56,440 --> 01:49:58,360
Congratulations.

1194
01:50:00,280 --> 01:50:02,880
Just what the hell
are you doing here?

1195
01:50:03,360 --> 01:50:06,440
You bring her to me bleeding,
and now you think you can talk to her?

1196
01:50:06,440 --> 01:50:09,000
Stay away from her.
Do you hear me?

1197
01:50:10,360 --> 01:50:13,240
There'll be a lot of confusion
in the race tomorrow, lad.

1198
01:50:13,240 --> 01:50:14,960
Someone could get shot.

1199
01:50:42,880 --> 01:50:47,360
Her beautiful eyes

1200
01:50:47,360 --> 01:50:51,000
Were a terrible curse

1201
01:50:51,000 --> 01:50:54,480
Three days in his grave

1202
01:50:54,480 --> 01:50:58,600
She ran off with his purse

1203
01:50:58,600 --> 01:51:03,000
They've got their land all picked out,
the pair of them.

1204
01:51:03,000 --> 01:51:06,560
The land of her dreams.
All those months...

1205
01:51:06,560 --> 01:51:10,200
l was trying to forget about her.

1206
01:51:12,200 --> 01:51:16,520
l was laying down the very track
that brought her here.

1207
01:51:22,000 --> 01:51:23,440
To hell with everyone.

1208
01:51:23,440 --> 01:51:27,840
l'm gonna get my land.
That's my thought for the night.

1209
01:51:27,840 --> 01:51:30,040
Tomorrow l ride for me.

1210
01:51:30,040 --> 01:51:31,960
Me alone.

1211
01:51:33,520 --> 01:51:35,320
And my horse.

1212
01:51:51,520 --> 01:51:54,520
Sweet Mary and Jesus...

1213
01:51:54,520 --> 01:51:56,520
and all the saints preserve us.

1214
01:51:58,920 --> 01:52:03,040
That there was the oldest horse
l ever saw in my life.

1215
01:52:57,880 --> 01:53:01,360
lt's almost noon.
We're gonna miss the photograph.

1216
01:53:01,360 --> 01:53:03,160
All right. Ready?

1217
01:53:17,960 --> 01:53:20,520
l sold him that horse.

1218
01:53:20,520 --> 01:53:22,720
Don't let him bluff you, cowboy!

1219
01:53:31,280 --> 01:53:34,240
We're breaking the law, Nora.

1220
01:53:34,240 --> 01:53:36,360
l don't like you taking charge
of the business side of our life.

1221
01:53:36,360 --> 01:53:39,320
Oh, you do too.
Now, listen up.

1222
01:53:39,320 --> 01:53:42,200
This stake goes into the ground
over there.

1223
01:53:42,200 --> 01:53:44,120
That's your job.
l'll tell you when.

1224
01:53:44,120 --> 01:53:47,000
l, meanwhile,
will run the horse around in circles.

1225
01:53:47,000 --> 01:53:49,000
He's got to look
all sweaty and tired.

1226
01:53:49,000 --> 01:53:52,480
- Even dead would be good. Got it?
- Yes.

1227
01:53:52,480 --> 01:53:56,000
But we don't really need
all of this.

1228
01:53:57,160 --> 01:53:58,800
lt's scary out here, Daniel.

1229
01:53:58,800 --> 01:54:02,240
Ah, we'll do fine.
Pretend we're starting out in life...

1230
01:54:02,240 --> 01:54:03,600
instead of ending up.

1231
01:54:23,560 --> 01:54:25,560
Anyone buy a good pair of spurs?

1232
01:54:28,520 --> 01:54:29,600
Sorry.

1233
01:54:33,600 --> 01:54:35,920
The race is that way, lad.

1234
01:54:48,880 --> 01:54:51,440
Forget the horse, lad...

1235
01:54:51,440 --> 01:54:53,560
and find yourself a donkey.

1236
01:55:01,320 --> 01:55:02,680
Take him by the bit.

1237
01:55:39,600 --> 01:55:41,240
Where the hell is he going?

1238
01:55:42,480 --> 01:55:43,720
Shoot him!

1239
01:55:53,000 --> 01:55:54,360
Fire!

1240
01:56:29,080 --> 01:56:30,440
Get up!

1241
01:56:52,000 --> 01:56:53,920
That way!

1242
01:57:01,600 --> 01:57:03,600
l have no wish to fight you.

1243
01:59:31,280 --> 01:59:33,520
God protect us!
Daniel, here they come!

1244
01:59:35,520 --> 01:59:39,840
Stand by, partner,
and pretend you're out of breath.

1245
01:59:39,840 --> 01:59:43,560
Pretend? My heart's
up here in my nose.

1246
01:59:46,440 --> 01:59:49,040
Oh, my God, Nora.
